236,Line 237,"Affordable Diagnostics  Our diagnostics business is always on  the lookout for ways to improve costs by  increasing efficiency in our manufacturing,  supply chain and product support areas.
"
237,Line 238,"Over  the past four years, we have realized year-over- year improvements in cost of goods for more  than 80% of products by volume.
"
238,Line 239,"Cost Savings Fund Innovation Throughout 2021, our sites took several steps  to improve operational efficiency, resulting in  cost savings that help drive our investment in  innovation.
"
239,Line 240,"For example: • • In Africa, we launched malaria diagnostic  tests with smaller packaging dimensions,  reducing required distribution trips and  lowering logistics costs by around 28% for  customers.
"
240,Line 241,"We also increased accessibility of  these products and helped ensure continuity  of supply by combining the supply  capabilities of our manufacturing facility in  China with those of our site in Korea.
"
241,Line 242,"• • Additionally, we completed a regulatory  submission for small-pack HIV diagnostic  tests.
"
242,Line 243,"The suggested reduction in kit  box dimensions will translate into  approximately 50% logistics cost savings  for customers as a result of improved  shipping efficiency.
"
243,Line 244,"• • To enable affordability for the governments  and agencies purchasing our Panbio  COVID-19 Antigen Self-Test, we have  improved materials and labor efficiency  and have achieved a 32% decrease in  manufacturing costs.
"
244,Line 245,"Additionally, the launch of a new diagnostic  product for traumatic brain injury (TBI) —  the i-STAT Alinity TBI Plasma — will enable  concussion diagnoses through blood tests.
"
245,Line 246,"This will reduce the need for expensive  CT scans, bringing down overall healthcare  costs following head injuries.
"
246,Line 247,"VALUE EMBEDDED BY DESIGN  One of Abbott’s Core Design Principles is  to optimize the products we create across  four factors: people reached, consumer  benefit, business and societal value.
"
247,Line 248,"Doing so  starts with understanding the needs of our  customers — from patients and healthcare  professionals to policymakers and those who  fund developments.
"
248,Line 249,"An important example of this principle in action  can be found in the Early Value Assessment  (EVA) process.
"
249,Line 250,"Through this process, we help  ensure the expectations of key stakeholders  are upheld even as we target increased access  and affordability.
"
250,Line 251,"Through the EVA, we proactively identify  steps that will drive economic and clinical value  for future products.
"
251,Line 252,"Recommendations are  then captured during design and development  processes; in turn, positively impacting future  reimbursement, coverage and access for patients.
"
252,Line 253,"DATA WORKFORCE ENVIRONMENT SUPPLY CHAIN GOVERNANCE QUALITY AND SAFETY ESG APPENDIX 2021 GLOBAL SUSTAINABILITY REPORT ABOUT  ACCESS AND AFFORDABILITY 20DIAGNOSTIC PANELS FOR  ENHANCED TREATMENT A diagnostic panel is a predetermined  group of medical tests used in the diagnosis  and treatment of disease.
"
253,Line 254,"Panels support  development of more effective treatments.
"
254,Line 255,"In 2021, we launched, or set the groundwork   for, three targeted panels.
"
255,Line 256,"• •  Antenatal Care (ANC) Panel: established   to improve lives and reduce mortality for   the 20 million mothers and children in high- burden countries through regular screening  and infection hotspot maps.
"
256,Line 257,"It supports the  World Health Organization’s mission to  eliminate mother-to-child transmission of  HIV, HBV and syphilis by 2030.
"
257,Line 258,"• •  Malnutrition Panel: research is underway to  improve well-being for children and pregnant  women, using biomarkers to identify  micronutrient deficiencies via clinical and   at-home tests.
"
258,Line 259,"Development of this panel   will continue into 2022 and beyond.
"
259,Line 260,"• • Fever Panel: development has started to  understand how biomarkers can help clinicians  better identify root causes of fever, enabling  proper treatment and care.
"
260,Line 261,"This will be  particularly important in pregnant women  and young children.
"
261,Line 262,"It will also aid infection  identification in patients with fever-like and  other “generic” symptoms.and acute respiratory infections.
"
262,Line 263,"These health  posts are also financially stable and will be able  to sustainably provide care for local residents.
"
263,Line 264,"During their second year of operation, these  posts generated an economic profit of 29%.
"
264,Line 265,"The study also demonstrated that access to  these health posts addressed a high demand  for these services in rural Rwanda.
"
265,Line 266,"As a means  to improving the health of Rwanda’s rural  population, these facilities are both improving  equity within Rwanda and providing a  roadmap for doing the same globally.
"
266,Line 267,"Transforming Virus Research   with Biomarkers  We have launched a hepatitis B virus (HBV)  biomarker program to expand understanding  of, and treatment for, patients with chronic  HBV .
"
267,Line 268,"Using HBV RNA and surface antigen  tests, we are conducting studies to inform  more effective treatments.
"
268,Line 269,"While research is  ongoing, evidence for the value of biomarkers  in moderating patient care has already been  shared in 14 publications.
