"
627,Line 628,"One way  we do this is by reducing our emissions,  finding more efficient ways to use energy  and limiting reliance on fossil fuels.
"
628,Line 629,"OUR IMPACT We realize our emissions contribute to global  climate change.
"
629,Line 630,"Our operational activities  produce Scope 1 (direct) and 2 (indirect)11  emissions.
"
630,Line 631,"Emissions from activities like business  travel, waste disposal, raw material sourcing and  processing, and product distribution, packaging  and disposal — collectively known as Scope 3  emissions — also contribute to our footprint.
"
631,Line 632,"We’re working to reduce the negative impacts  of our emissions by investing in renewable  energy, reducing fleet fuel consumption,  increasing manufacturing efficiency and  partnering with suppliers.
"
632,Line 633,"OUR MANAGEMENT APPROACH  We maintain a robust program for recording  and reducing energy and air emissions,  outlined in both our Climate Responsible  Energy Policy and Internal Energy Guidelines.
"
633,Line 634,"Along with these documents, our Global EHS  Governance team provides guidance on: • • Energy efficiency in   manufacturing operations • • Low-carbon energy investments  • • Transportation fleet efficiency • • Supply chain carbon footprint  • • Public reporting of our performance  We align with international frameworks —  including CDP and the Greenhouse Gas (GHG)  Protocol — to measure, track, reduce and   report emissions.
"
634,Line 635,"11 Scope 1 emissions result from owned and controlled sources.
"
635,Line 636,"Scope 2  emissions are produced during generation of purchased electricity  and energy.
"
636,Line 637,"DATA WORKFORCE SUPPLY CHAIN GOVERNANCE QUALITY AND SAFETY ESG APPENDIX 2021 GLOBAL SUSTAINABILITY REPORT ABOUT ACCESS AND AFFORDABILITY  ENVIRONMENT 43A Holistic Plan for Reductions  We are committed to supporting the Science  Based Targets initiative (SBTi) objective.
"
637,Line 638,"By  2030, we plan to reduce Scope 1 and 2 emissions  by 30%12 (vs.
