701,Line 702,"Managing Water Risks Our water management technical  standard helps monitor Abbott’s impact  on resources in communities where we  operate.
"
702,Line 703,"Any manufacturing or research and  development (R&D) site with high water-use  requirements15 — as well as those in water- stressed areas — must implement management  plans and targets for mitigating risks.
"
703,Line 704,"Significant water users must also engage key  local stakeholders to fully understand water- related risks.
"
704,Line 705,"Abbott sites are evaluated annually for  resilience, using WRI AqueductTM — a global  water-risk mapping tool — to analyze local  water stress and evaluate against our internal  water use intensity.
"
705,Line 706,"The assessment also  highlights our company-wide level of risk and,  today, shows our overall exposure to chronic  physical risks is limited.
"
706,Line 707,"Read more about how we manage water risks  in our CDP Water Disclosure Response .
