775,Line 776,"Reduce  At both the Abbott Park corporate  headquarters and Core Diagnostics operations  in Illinois, we started an initiative in March  2021 to reduce waste generation from these  sites by sending baled corrugated cardboard to  a third party for beneficial use.
"
776,Line 777,"The cardboard  is used as cellulose insulation for homes and  commercial buildings.
"
777,Line 778,"While pushing the  management of this material further up the  waste hierarchy increased our overall costs  rather than providing cost savings, it resulted  in a waste reduction of nearly 200 U.S. tons  (193.5 U.S. tons) for these locations in 2021.
"
778,Line 779,"We are continuing this initiative after 2021 and  project over 200 U.S. tons of baled corrugated  cardboard will be sent to the third party for  beneficial use every year going forward.
"
779,Line 780,"Reuse  In Costa Rica, our team is finding ways to reuse  Gaylord shipping containers, cutting both waste  production and costs associated with product  distribution.
"
780,Line 781,"For health and safety purposes,  containers have historically been used once.
"
781,Line 782,"However, our studies found that, with proper  sterilization methods, each container could  be used twice before being disposed of.
"
782,Line 783,"The  team is now in the process of transitioning to  multi-use, updating procedures for handling  the shipping containers and assessing their  condition prior to reuse.
"
783,Line 784,"Recycle  In one of our U.S. nutrition plants, prior to  COVID-19, fiber drums were sent to an external  partner for beneficial reuse (resale).
"
784,Line 785,"During  the pandemic, these vendor activities slowed,  resulting in the accumulation of fiber drums  at our on-site Recycle Center.
"
785,Line 786,"In response,  we invested in a dechimer machine to break  drums down into their cardboard and metal  components so each can be recycled.
"
786,Line 787,"In  2021, about 13.7 U.S. tons of fiber drums were processed by the dechimer, and this investment  prevented surplus drums from being sent  for incineration.
"
787,Line 788,"In addition, now that fiber  drums are back to being sent to an external  partner for beneficial use, we are still using the  dechimer to break down lower-quality drums  that the vendor cannot take, which will result  in an estimated 4.8 U.S. tons per year increase  in recycling, and corresponding decrease in  incineration, of fiber drums.
"
788,Line 789,"See page 107 for a detailed breakdown of our  waste metrics.
"
789,Line 790,"DATA WORKFORCE SUPPLY CHAIN GOVERNANCE QUALITY AND SAFETY ESG APPENDIX 2021 GLOBAL SUSTAINABILITY REPORT ABOUT ACCESS AND AFFORDABILITY  ENVIRONMENT 51Packaging Packaging is key to ensuring our life- saving solutions are delivered safely to  those who need them.
"
790,Line 791,"To achieve our  2030 goals, we continually assess our  design and manufacturing processes,  identifying novel ways to develop  packaging solutions that protect both  their contents and the planet.
"
791,Line 792,"OUR IMPACT  We recognize the impact our packaging has  on the environment in the form of resource  use, related emissions and waste production.
"
792,Line 793,"We are rethinking how we design packaging  to optimize material use and keep materials in  circulation for as long as possible.
"
793,Line 794,"To reduce  our raw material burden, we are optimizing  efficiency by minimizing the volume and  weight of our packaging.
"
794,Line 795,"We are also  employing circularity principles to incorporate  increased quantities of recycled content and  designing for recyclability, reusability and  increasingly positive impact.
"
795,Line 796,"OUR MANAGEMENT APPROACH  We want to design our packaging with  sustainability in mind.
"
796,Line 797,"Many Abbott functions  collaborate to help ensure sustainability  considerations are prioritized during product  and packaging design and manufacture.
"
797,Line 798,"Each division has provided projections for  the next decade of packaging projects.
"
798,Line 799,"Our  Sustainable Packaging Council has designed a  database for reporting progress against these  projections, supporting more efficient tracking  of our target.
"
799,Line 800,"Guiding Principles of Sustainable Packaging  To address 50 million pounds of packaging  through high-impact sustainable design  programs, we need a plan of action.
"
800,Line 801,"Our  Sustainable Packaging Guiding Principles —  recently created by the Sustainable Packaging  Council — inform changes to existing  packaging and target new designs that integrate  sustainability from the very beginning.
"
801,Line 802,"The Sustainable Packaging Guiding  Principles are: Optimize Material Efficiency • • Eliminate unnecessary components  • • Reduce packaging materials Employ Circularity Principles • • Replace problematic materials  • • Design for disassembly  • • Design for recyclability  • • Design for reuse  • • Utilize renewable materials   • • Integrate recycled content Balance All Aspects of Packaging   Systems Holistically • • Optimize cube efficiency  • • Provide consumer direction  • • Improve carbon footprintWorking With Suppliers We’re working with suppliers to create lower  impact packaging that supports our circular  economy approach.
"
802,Line 803,"The Sustainable Packaging Guiding  Principles are: Optimize Material Efficiency • • Eliminate unnecessary components  • • Reduce packaging materials Employ Circularity Principles • • Replace problematic materials  • • Design for disassembly  • • Design for recyclability  • • Design for reuse  • • Utilize renewable materials   • • Integrate recycled content Balance All Aspects of Packaging   Systems Holistically • • Optimize cube efficiency  • • Provide consumer direction  • • Improve carbon footprintWorking With Suppliers We’re working with suppliers to create lower  impact packaging that supports our circular  economy approach.
"
803,Line 804,"Together, we identify  solutions that either eliminate packaging  materials supplied to us or ensure those we  do receive can be reused in manufacturing  processes.
"
804,Line 805,"This includes optimizing design  to reduce material use — particularly  plastics — improving shipping efficiencies,  increasing fiber-based packaging sustainability  and introducing reusable options.
"
805,Line 806,"We are  also working to develop packaging take- back initiatives.
"
