807,Line 808,"OUR 2021 PERFORMANCE  Through adoption and socialization of  the 2030 packaging goal, a list of high- impact packaging projects was developed  and prioritized, and the projected benefits  quantified.
"
808,Line 809,"Implementation of these projects  will contribute to achieving our goal on time.Same Packaging, Fewer Materials  One way we’re reducing our packaging  footprint is by finding solutions to do  more with less.
"
809,Line 810,"We recently launched  the first phase of a project to reduce  plastic use in blister packaging for our  acetaminophen product.
"
810,Line 811,"Through the project, we are reducing  packaging specifications from a starting  thickness of 250 micron of plastic to  220 micron.
"
811,Line 812,"The result is a 16.2 metric  ton reduction in material use with  associated savings of $93,000 annually.
"
812,Line 813,"NEARLY 300,pounds of packaging reduced  in 2021 through optimizing  material efficiency NEARLY 15,pounds impacted in 2021 through  employing circularity principles DATA WORKFORCE SUPPLY CHAIN GOVERNANCE QUALITY AND SAFETY ESG APPENDIX 2021 GLOBAL SUSTAINABILITY REPORT ABOUT ACCESS AND AFFORDABILITY  ENVIRONMENT 52Optimizing Materials Use  In 2021, several projects were implemented to  reduce packaging size while retaining the same   level of protection.
"
813,Line 814,"To increase the efficiency of our Core Diagnostics  Alinity platform, engineers identified an opportunity  to improve packaging design through carton size  reductions for Alinity I and Alinity C products.
"
814,Line 815,"Based  on the portfolio conversion, these changes are  predicted to have a 2022 sustainability impact of: • • 170 fewer truckloads from Abbott  manufacturing sites to the distribution center  • • 240,000 pound reduction in total carton weight  • • 56,000 pound reduction in total shipper weight • • 270 loaded shipping containers removed from  the global distribution network A similar initiative was identified for our Sigma  Strong ARCHITECT Clinical Chemistry product  line.
"
815,Line 816,"By implementing more appropriately sized  packaging options for assays, we have significantly  increased efficiency for material use, and product  transportation and storage.
"
816,Line 817,"In 2021 alone, 3,000  pounds of packaging materials were eliminated   while transport requirements were cut by 30%.
