1080,Line 1081,"Chemicals of Environmental Concern and  Antimicrobial Resistance Abbott’s branded generic medicines business  assesses suppliers operating in at-risk regions23  that handle and/or manufacture chemicals  of environmental concern and Active  Pharmaceutical Ingredients (APIs).
"
1081,Line 1082,"Abbott  is a small player in the global anti-infectives  market, but recognizes our role in limiting  antimicrobial resistance.
"
1082,Line 1083,"This assessment evaluates suppliers based on  supply chain criticality and environmental,  health and safety risk.
"
1083,Line 1084,"Suppliers are evaluated  via a questionnaire depending on the level of  risk assigned.
"
1084,Line 1085,"An on-site visit24 may be triggered if a supplier  is determined high-risk from questionnaire  review, if it’s had a significant incident,  received notice of violation or negative media  reporting, or is identified by one of our internal  stakeholders.
"
1085,Line 1086,"Upon completion of the on-site  assessment, suppliers are assigned a risk status  and follow-up actions are determined, including  CAPA execution by the supplier, continuation  of business activities, identification of back-up  suppliers and/or implementation of an exit  strategy.
"
1086,Line 1087,"By assessing suppliers this way, we aim  to minimize environmental risks and ensure  business continuity.
"
1087,Line 1088,"In 2021, 48 self-assessments were completed  by suppliers.
"
1088,Line 1089,"On-site visits of 39 suppliers —  16 of which were desk-based as a result of  COVID — were completed by Abbott or third- party subject matter experts.
"
