1251,Line 1252,"DATA WORKFORCE ENVIRONMENT SUPPLY CHAIN QUALITY AND SAFETY ESG APPENDIX 2021 GLOBAL SUSTAINABILITY REPORT ABOUT ACCESS AND AFFORDABILITY  GOVERNANCE 79Rigorous Auditing and Monitoring  Our international audit and monitoring  process assesses compliance with our  code, policies and procedures.
"
1252,Line 1253,"Assessments  determine the frequency and scope of audits.
"
1253,Line 1254,"We maintain a tracking system for all action  items identified to ensure business leaders are  held accountable for making any necessary  improvements to processes in a timely manner.
"
1254,Line 1255,"The OEC monitors business activities  throughout the year.
"
1255,Line 1256,"OEC personnel  supporting each Abbott business unit and  country perform an annual risk assessment  to identify areas of potential compliance risk.
"
1256,Line 1257,"Based on assessment outcomes, they then  establish monitoring plans for the year.
"
1257,Line 1258,"Our monitoring includes selecting a risk-based  sampling of interactions with healthcare  providers (HCPs) (such as educational events,  engagements with HCPs for services, and  provision of sample or evaluation product) and  reviewing supporting documentation to assess  compliance with Abbott’s policies.
"
1258,Line 1259,"The OEC also conducts “live monitoring”  programs through which personnel directly  observe HCP interactions.
"
1259,Line 1260,"Issues detected  through monitoring are analyzed, investigated if necessary and reported to management.
"
1260,Line 1261,"Monitoring data are analyzed and trended over  time to identify potential patterns requiring  further evaluation.
"
1261,Line 1262,"The OEC assigns and tracks  to completion remedial actions, addressing the  root causes of monitoring findings.
"
1262,Line 1263,"Processes for Investigations and   Corrective Actions  All reports of potential code violations —  including those related to discrimination and  harassment — by employees and third parties  that perform certain services on our behalf  are thoroughly investigated.
"
1263,Line 1264,"Where necessary,  corrective actions are taken.
"
1264,Line 1265,"Any employee  who violates our code, policies or procedures  is subject to appropriate disciplinary action,  which may include termination.
"
1265,Line 1266,"Employees  refusing to cooperate in an investigation —   or anyone who knowingly reports a false  concern, or one intended to threaten,  intimidate or retaliate — may also be subject   to disciplinary action.
"
1266,Line 1267,"Abbott does not tolerate retaliation against  whistleblowers, or anyone else who reports  a violation in good faith.
"
1267,Line 1268,"This foundational  principle is embedded in several sections  of our Code of Business Conduct, which employees are required to certify their  adherence to annually.
"
1268,Line 1269,"Our training courses  on the Code of Business Conduct and Decision  Making at Abbott also make reference to  Abbott’s stance on no retaliation.
"
1269,Line 1270,"Anti- retaliation language is also included in our  Global Compliance Policy on Reporting  Concerns and our Global Compliance  Standards.
"
1270,Line 1271,"Anti-retaliation principles are also  a key component in several human resource  policies, including Employee Problem Solving,  Workplace Harassment and Violence in the  Workplace.
"
1271,Line 1272,"Abbott’s Speak-Up platform,  where employees and third parties can raise  potential concerns, includes a message from  Abbott’s CECO that Abbott does not tolerate  retaliation against those who report concerns.
"
1272,Line 1273,"In addition, Abbott encourages employees to  report any instances of retaliation, separately  investigates those reports and disciplines  employees who have engaged in retaliation.
"
1273,Line 1274,"Corrective action related to Code violations,  including retaliation, may involve disciplinary  action up to and including termination.
