1519,Line 1520,"(e)  Legacy Alere is included in Health and Safety and Scope 3 metrics beginning in 2019.
"
1520,Line 1521,"2018 metrics do not include legacy Alere.
"
1521,Line 1522,"(f)  Annual incident rates are calculated per 100 employees, assuming the average employee works 40 hours per week and 50 weeks per year.
"
1522,Line 1523,"This is  equivalent to 200,000 hours worked.
"
1523,Line 1524,"(g) This change represents 2021 progress toward our 2030 Goal of 30% reduction from 2018.
"
1524,Line 1525,"(h) This is the percentage change from 2020 to 2021.
"
1525,Line 1526,"(i) This is the baseline year.
"
1526,Line 1527,"(j) Progress toward 2030 carbon goal is reported using the GHGP Scope 2 market-based methodology.
"
1527,Line 1528,"(k)  Scope 2 emissions are calculated using the GHGP market-based methodology.
"
1528,Line 1529,"Per the GHGP, where market-based information is not available,  location-based results have been used as proxy.
"
1529,Line 1530,"(l)  Reported Purchased Fuels Scope 1 sources consist of fuel consumed by manufacturing, R&D and warehouse facilities under Abbott’s control; sales  fleet; and Abbott-owned aviation.
"
1530,Line 1531,"(m) Per the GHGP, Scope 1 Refrigerant CO 2e emissions include only those covered in the Kyoto Protocol.
"
1531,Line 1532,"(n)  Reported Scope 2 sources consist of energy directly purchased by Abbott, such as electricity, steam, and hot and chilled water, as well as emissions  from leased locations.
"
1532,Line 1533,"Unless specified otherwise, emissions are calculated according to the GHGP Scope 2 location-based method.(o)  Abbott’s nonenergy-consumption greenhouse gas emissions, such as refrigerant releases and process air emissions, are omitted.
"
1533,Line 1534,"The total CO 2  equivalents from nonenergy sources are noted in the Total Emissions (Scope 1 and 2) table.
"
1534,Line 1535,"(p)  All Scope 3 calculations are adjusted to account for updated spend metrics.
"
1535,Line 1536,"Sourcing category spend allocations are subject to change year over year  in alignment with business strategy.
"
1536,Line 1537,"Legacy Alere included in metrics beginning in 2019.
"
1537,Line 1538,"2018 metrics do not include legacy Alere.
"
1538,Line 1539,"(q) This reflects emissions from fuel combusted by manufacturing, R&D and warehouse facilities under Abbott’s control.
"
1539,Line 1540,"(r)  Water-stressed locations have been determined using the WRI Aqueduct™ global water risk mapping tool.
"
1540,Line 1541,"Sites rated as having high or extremely  high baseline water stress in the tool are classified as being water stressed.
"
1541,Line 1542,"(s) Water withdrawal is equivalent to water intake.
"
1542,Line 1543,"(t)  Abbott’s diversion rate is calculated as follows: (Total Waste + Beneficial Use - Landfilled and Incineration without Energy Recovery)/Total Waste +  Beneficial Use.
"
1543,Line 1544,"Commercial and other building activities, specific to beneficial use, are included in this rate starting in 2019.
"
1544,Line 1545,"(u)  In 2018, data represents manufacturing, R&D and warehouse facilities under Abbott’s control.
"
1545,Line 1546,"Nonmanufacturing data was not collected prior   to 2019.
"
1546,Line 1547,"(v) Waste-generation data does not include materials that are reused beneficially.
"
1547,Line 1548,"(w)  Abbott defines beneficial-use activities as sending material that otherwise would have been wasted off site to be used as an effective substitute for a  commercial product or commodity.
"
1548,Line 1549,"Beneficial-use material is used as is or in substantially the same form as it was generated.
"
1549,Line 1550,"(x)  The definition of “government agency inspection” was updated in 2017 by Abbott to include routine visits and sample collection from regulatory  agencies or designated representatives.
