1750,Line 1751,"Clinical Trial Registrations   Abbott registers all applicable and/or covered clinical trials, regardless of outcome, in a publicly accessible clinical  trials registry, such as ClinicalTrials.gov .
"
1751,Line 1752,"For branded generic pharmaceuticals, this means that we register  interventional clinical studies in patients as designated by national laws and regulations.
"
1752,Line 1753,"For medical devices and  diagnostics, this means we register interventional clinical studies of health outcomes and pediatric post-marketing  surveillance studies, as designated by national laws and regulations.
"
1753,Line 1754,"Clinical Trial Results Disclosures   Abbott is committed to transparency and sharing important information about the clinical trials we sponsor.
"
1754,Line 1755,"We  recognize that there are important public health benefits to making clinical trial information available to healthcare  providers, patients and the public.
"
1755,Line 1756,"Our registrations and results disclosures adhere to all applicable national laws and  regulations in countries where we operate.
"
1756,Line 1757,"Abbott discloses the results of all applicable or covered clinical trials as described above, regardless of outcome,  in a publicly accessible clinical trials results database, such as ClinicalTrials.gov.
"
1757,Line 1758,"We also report the results of  any exploratory pharmaceutical clinical studies if the findings have significant medical importance, such as with  important safety findings.
